# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .dockerignore — keep secrets, build artifacts, and noise out of
# every image we build. Applies to ALL Dockerfile builds in this repo
# regardless of which target stage (dev / prod) is being assembled.
#
# Defense in depth: even though Dockerfile.backend's prod stage uses
# explicit `COPY src/ src/` + `COPY config/ config/` (so it can't
# accidentally include .env), the dev stage uses `COPY . .` which
# WOULD pull in everything. This file protects both.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secrets — must NEVER end up in an image layer ──
.env
.env.*
secrets/
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx

# ── Local runtime state — bloats images, leaks data ──
data/
backups/
reports/
error/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# ── VCS / IDE / OS noise ──
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# ── Python build / cache ──
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/

# ── Node / frontend build artifacts ──
# (rebuilt fresh inside the image)
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.vite/
node_modules/

# ── Docs and research artifacts not needed at runtime ──
# Backend prod doesn't COPY docs/ so this is safety; frontend prod
# doesn't copy them either. Also avoids the heavy generated PDFs.
# NOTE: README.md is intentionally NOT excluded because Dockerfile.backend
# does `COPY pyproject.toml README.md ./` (hatchling needs it for the wheel build).
docs/
CLAUDE.md
LICENSE

# ── Compose / dockerfile (no need to ship into images) ──
docker-compose*.yml
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore
Makefile

# ── Tests — not needed in prod runtime images ──
tests/
src/tests/
**/test_*.py

# ── Misc ──
*.log
.env.example
